column23:
Ascension Ebenezer Health Resource Center brings community partners and resources in a collaborative and effective manner to support our goal. The goal focuses on two major health areas: Chronic Diseases and Food Insecurities. The Center is staffed by two registered nurses, nurse practitioner, social worker and community outreach personnel.

Additionally, the Center includes a food pantry in response to the growing need for food resources. The Ascension Ebenezer Food Pantry provides healthy food options like low-salt, low-carbohydrate, less-processed foods along with more fresh fruit and vegetables then most food pantries in the area. Each month, the pantry serves 600 households --55% of which have a member with high blood pressure, and 31% of which have a member with diabetes.

column23: We are opening our physical buildings for our students that donâ€™t have a quiet learning environment to take the AP exam from May 13-May 22. Our mission is to Graduate all learners as critical thinkers, self directed learners prepared for college, careers, family life and community involvement. College Board communicated that AP exams will be administered online this year given the Covid-19 crisis. Itâ€™s likely that more privileged students are set up to receive high scores and at-risk or low-income black and brown students will be much more likely to receive low or no scores at all. While there has always been some level of disparity historically in AP test results, many of the levers that high-performing schools have to support underprivileged students are gone in the current testing scenarios. We are committed to providing our students a quiet learning environment where they can assess. We know that our students have worked hard to prep for these exams in order to gain college credit and reduce their financial burden. We are still gathering the final numbers but the max per assessment is 15 students, approx 200 students + our 30 staff volunteers. In total we will need 250-300 masks to provide staff and students May 13-May 22. Please let me know if this is possible.
